Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: THE COMPANY AND CERTAIN SUBSIDIARIES, AS INDICATED ABOVE, ARE EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501 OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND A SIMILAR PROVISION OF STATE LAW. HOWEVER, THE COMPANY AND THE SUBSIDIARIES ARE SUBJECT TO FEDERAL INCOME TAX ON ANY UNRELATED BUSINESS TAXABLE INCOME. SOME OF THE COMPANY'S SUBSIDIARIES ARE SUBJECT TO FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAX. DURING 2010 AND 2009, THESE ENTITIES HAD NET OPERATING LOSSES AND INCURRED NO TAX LIABILITY. OTHER OF THE COMPANY'S SUBSIDIARIES ARE ORGANIZED AS ARKANSAS LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANIES AND ARE NOT DIRECTLY SUBJECT TO INCOME TAXES UNDER THE PROVISIONS OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND APPLICABLE STATE LAWS. THEREFORE, TAXABLE INCOME OR LOSS IS REPORTED TO THE INDIVIDUAL PARTNERS FOR INCLUSION IN THEIR RESPECTIVE TAX RETURNS AND NO PROVISION FOR FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAXES HAS BEEN INCLUDED IN THE ACCOMPANYING CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE COMPANY ADOPTED THE PROVISIONS OF ASC TOPIC 740 (ASC 740), ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES, ON SEPTEMBER 30, 2010. NO AMOUNTS WERE RECORDED AS A RESULT OF THE IMPLEMENTATION OF ASC 740.

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AUDITED BY AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT ON A CONSOLIDATED BASIS. THE AUDIT COMMITTEE OF ST. BERNARDS HEALTHCARE, INC. ASSUMES RESPONSIBILITY FOR OVERSIGHT OF THE AUDIT OF THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND SELECTION OF AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT.

ST. BERNARDS HEALTHCARE, INC. IS THE SOLE MEMBER OF ST. BERNARDS VILLAGE. THE DIRECTORS OF THE CORPORATION SHALL AT ALL TIMES BE LIMITED TO INDIVIDUALS WHO ARE EITHER MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF ST. BERNARDS HEALTHCARE, INC. OR NONMEMBERS OF SUCH BOARD WHO HAVE THE APPROVAL OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF ST. BERNARDS HEALTHCARE, INC. ST. BERNARDS HEALTHCARE, INC. MUST APPROVE ANY TRANSACTION OVER $1 MILLION. THE DIOCESE OF LITTLE ROCK MUST APPROVE ANY TRANSACTION OVER $5 MILLION.

THE FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE FOLLOWING PERSONS OR GROUPS: CONTROLLER OF ST. BERNARDS HEALTHCARE, INC., VICE PRESIDENT OF FINANCE OF ST. BERNARDS HEALTHCARE, INC., PRESIDENT/CEO OF ST. BERNARDS HEALTHCARE, INC., LEGAL COUNSEL, AND THE AUDIT COMMITTEE OF ST. BERNARDS HEALTHCARE, INC. PRIOR TO FILING.

DIRECTORS AND ABOVE ANNUALLY SUBMIT A WRITTEN STATEMENT DISCLOSING ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. MANAGEMENT INVESTIGATES ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS AND TAKES APPROPRIATE ACTION DEPENDING ON THE NATURE OF THE CONFLICT. LEGAL COUNSEL ALSO REVIEWS ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST AND ADVISES MANAGEMENT.

THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS SELECTS DIRECTORS TO SERVE ON THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE. THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE APPROVES THE INITIAL SALARY AND ANY SUBSEQUENT SALARY ADJUSTMENTS OF ALL MANAGEMENT. THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE OBTAINS AN INDEPENDENT SALARY SURVEY FROM CLARK CONSULTING ON AN ANNUAL BASIS FOR USE IN DETERMINING THE APPROPRIATE SALARY RANGES FOR MANAGEMENT. THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE PRESENTS THE INFORMATION TO THE BOARD FOR APPROVAL. IN 2009, ALL MANAGEMENT PERSONNEL AND ALL OTHER EMPLOYEES OF THE ORGANIZATION WERE REVIEWED BY CLARK CONSULTING.
THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ARE NOT MADE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC.
